            <p class="text-sm text-rose-900 font-medium"><strong>The time cost:</strong> Spent 14 hours building on free tiers across all platforms. When limits hit, spent another 8 hours migrating to paid plans. Could've just started with paid and saved those 14 hours.</p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The exception:</strong> Relume. Actually free for planning‚Äîunlimited sitemaps and wireframes. But Relume doesn't build sites, it plans them. You still need Framer or Webflow to actually launch. Free planning tool, not a free builder.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Subdomain Problem</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Every free AI builder forces you onto a subdomain. Your site lives at their URL, not yours:
      </p>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg mb-4">
        <code class="text-sm">yoursite.wixsite.com</code><br>
        <code class="text-sm">yoursite.framer.app</code><br>
        <code class="text-sm">yoursite.durable.co</code>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This matters more than you think:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li><strong>Trust:</strong> Visitors notice subdomains. Looks amateur, temporary, or spammy. 47% of users say they'd trust a .com more than a builder subdomain.</li>
        <li><strong>SEO:</strong> Google ranks subdomains lower. All else equal, yoursite.com beats yoursite.wixsite.com every time.</li>
        <li><strong>Branding:</strong> You're building the builder's brand, not yours. Every visitor sees "wixsite.com" and thinks "template site."</li>
        <li><strong>Portability:</strong> If you leave, you can't take the subdomain with you. Your backlinks, your search rankings, your traffic‚Äîstuck on their domain.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Custom domains cost $10-15/year from registrars like Namecheap. Most AI builders charge extra to connect one ($10-20/year). But it's worth it. For serious projects, don't skip this.
      </p>
    </section>

