    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">The "Freemium" Strategy Explained</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Why do AI builders offer free tiers? It's not charity. It's a calculated business strategy called "freemium"‚Äîgive away a limited version to hook users, then convert them to paying customers.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        <strong>The math works like this:</strong> For every 100 free users, 3-5 convert to paid. Those paying customers subsidize the free ones. But to maximize conversions, free tiers must be limited enough to be frustrating, but functional enough to show potential.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        <strong>The result:</strong> Free tiers are designed to push you toward upgrades. Page limits, storage limits, feature gates‚Äîthese aren't technical constraints, they're business decisions. You're supposed to hit the wall and pay.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        <strong>Is this bad?</strong> No, it's smart business. But understand what you're getting into. Free tiers are marketing tools, not products. Use them accordingly.
      </p>
    </section>

